modules.description: This module provides operations for constructing and transforming formatted document fragments through combinators like appending, joining, and indentation-aware mapping, supporting dynamic assembly of structured content. It works with abstract representations of templates (`t`), mutable formatting buffers, and compiled templates that allow keyed value substitution, enabling use cases such as generating source code, markup, or configuration files with precise layout control. The design emphasizes stateful buffer manipulation and delayed evaluation of template parameters to facilitate complex formatting workflows.
